The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Trade Unions and the National Federation of Working Commissions will set up a strike commission on Friday to coordinate the Monday strike that will last indefinitely.
On Saturday a protest rally will be held, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stop will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, as rail traffic will be completely stopped and workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike until 13 o'clock.
In the afternoon of Friday, the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike to be held in conjunction with the National Federation of Working Committees.
The strike commission of the Liga and the National Workers' Union will also be set up to coordinate the actions of Monday.
On Saturday a protest rally will be held, while on Monday the participating unions will be pronounced in an indefinite strike, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly rejects public health law, trade unions will immediately withdraw their appeal to the strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the agenda for Monday of the National Assembly, it is also possible that only the public health law may be voted on at very late evening hours, or at best near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: in the railways you will stop working for indefinite time, in the morning you may stop part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the interurban bus transport of the Volán companies.
At the same time, at many points in the country there will be a closure of half the roads.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League website.
Some unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for defined time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) were unable to reach agreement even on minimum services, although, as Christmas parties are approaching, they are increasingly the people who travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the start of the day until 13 o'clock, the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike, the Budapest airports from 7 to 9 o'clock in the morning, will hold a four-hour strike of the LIGA Trade Unions of Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the Teacher Trade Unions called for a 2-hour strike and the 2- to 8-hour Democratic Union of Educators.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will take a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Workers of the Health and Social Sector (SDTSSS), which is part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraws its proposal on public health reform and puts a new conception into a social debate.
The second demand is to gradually introduce the new form of calculation of pensions which will enter into force next year.
The third is to ensure that, even before 2010, in the case of early pensions, the possibility of occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Trade Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economics and Transport on the railway lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country there is increased risk by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division) of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August of this year with the support of the Movement by a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from a number of points of view.
The company's "risk warning" writes: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the fact that "with the worsening of ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsies of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic confrontations may occur."
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this character - the representative of the research institute added.
They stated that all this was due to one of the main shortcomings of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on existing gypsies and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, prevents normal dialogue, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country".
They remind us that, starting in the autumn of 2006, the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups of Hungary has been increasingly promoted and that since the summer of 2007, numerous organizations have been established in the country that are self-definite of "national self-defence associations".
"The common feature of these groupings is that they are self-defined as civil organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defence - even armed - (civil defence, national defence, defence of public order), referring to the ineptitudes of the police, the army, that is to say of the State" - they add.
