The party isn't always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law defines precisely the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holiday days - that the coming year will be less - are reorganized working days.
Not even in the EU or North America, parties are unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national party, state party and holidays.
The holidays are fundamentally related to religious festivals and historical ephemerals.
Let us also celebrate the New Year: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter above all so that they can rest those who spent celebrating the old year.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national festival on 15 March in memory of the revolution of 1848 and on 23 October, the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On 20 August we celebrate the foundation of the State, on 1 May the work party, on 1 and 2 November we remember our dead relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country there are two-day parties the Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious parties rarely coincide with a weekend, so often they become bridges when there is only one working day before or after the party.
In exchange for extended weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
He is the minister of work who regulates in his specific decree when you have to work exactly in exchange for the day directly before or after the feast.
This legal standard is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public servants.
It is not mandatory, on the other hand, for companies and service institutions that, because of their role, work continuously even during holidays.
This year the order of work can only be altered around the holidays of the year: from December 24, life is practically stopped in the country, since according to the experiences, most people "make bridges" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
